%%{init: {'theme': 'dark', 'themeVariables': { 'fontFamily': 'Inter, sans-serif' }}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Terminal / User
    participant CLI as GWS Core
    participant Cache as Local Cache (~/.config/gws)
    participant Discovery as Google Discovery Service
    participant API as Google Workspace APIs
    participant Armor as Cloud Model Armor

    rect rgb(31, 41, 55)
        note right of User: Phase 1: Dynamic Tree Construction
        User->>CLI: Execute: gws drive files list
        CLI->>CLI: Read argv[1] (Service = 'drive')
        
        CLI->>Cache: Check for cached Discovery Doc
        alt Cache Miss or Expired (>24h)
            CLI->>Discovery: Fetch Discovery Document for 'drive'
            Discovery-->>CLI: Return JSON Schema
            CLI->>Cache: Write schema to cache
        else Cache Hit
            Cache-->>CLI: Return cached schema
        end

        CLI->>CLI: Build clap::Command tree dynamically
    end

    rect rgb(55, 65, 81)
        note right of User: Phase 2: Execution & Authentication
        CLI->>CLI: Re-parse remaining argv (files list --params ...)
        CLI->>Cache: Read OAuth Credentials / Tokens
        CLI->>CLI: Construct HTTP Request & Sign Headers
        
        CLI->>API: Execute HTTPS Request
        API-->>CLI: Return JSON Response
    end

    rect rgb(31, 41, 55)
        note right of User: Phase 3: Agent Safety & Output
        opt --sanitize flag or GOOGLE_WORKSPACE_CLI_SANITIZE_TEMPLATE is set
            CLI->>Armor: Send API JSON Response for prompt injection scan
            Armor-->>CLI: Return sanitized JSON or Block
        end
        CLI-->>User: Output structured JSON
    end
